<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Dynamic Dropdown Arrow</title>
    <style>
        .custom-select {
            position: relative;
            display: inline-block;
            width: auto;
        }

        .custom-select select {
            appearance: none; /* Hide default arrow */
            -webkit-appearance: none;
            -moz-appearance: none;
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 16px;
            background-color: white;
        }

        .custom-select::after {
            content: "▼"; /* Custom dropdown arrow */
            position: absolute;
            right: 10px; /* Default position */
            top: 50%;
            transform: translateY(-50%);
            pointer-events: none;
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #555;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="custom-select">
    <select id="dynamicSelect">
        <option>Short</option>
        <option>Medium Length</option>
        <option>Very Very Long Option Text</option>
    </select>
</div>

<script>
    function adjustArrowPosition() {
        const select = document.getElementById("dynamicSelect");
        const selectWidth = select.offsetWidth; 
        const selectedOptionText = select.options[select.selectedIndex].text;
        const textLength = selectedOptionText.length;

        // Adjust the padding and arrow position dynamically
        let paddingRight = Math.max(30, textLength * 5); // Dynamically adjust padding based on text length
        select.style.paddingRight = `${paddingRight}px`;

        // Update the arrow position (for wider select elements)
        document.querySelector(".custom-select::after").style.right = `${paddingRight - 20}px`;
    }

    // Adjust on change
    document.getElementById("dynamicSelect").addEventListener("change", adjustArrowPosition);
    // Adjust on page load
    window.addEventListener("load", adjustArrowPosition);
</script>

</body>
</html>
How It Works:
Hides the default browser arrow using appearance: none;.
Adds a custom arrow via ::after pseudo-element.
Dynamically adjusts the right padding of the <select> based on the length of the selected option's text.
Moves the arrow dynamically by adjusting right based on text width.
This way, the arrow moves closer for shorter words and further for longer words, maintaining a natural padding without unnecessary spacing. 🚀







